summary: This is a search and seizure warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York, authorizing the search of a large multi-story residence in New York, NY. The warrant is related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy, and it commands law enforcement to seize evidence related to occupancy, ownership, and the layout of the premises.

persons.name: Barbara Moses
persons.context: Issued and signed the search and seizure warrant for the Subject Premises.

events.title: Issuance of Search Warrant
events.description: A federal search and seizure warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses for a large multi-story residence in New York, NY, related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy violations.

locations: Subject Premises: a nearly 19,000 square foot multi-story single-family residence in New York, New York
keyFacts: The search warrant targets a nearly 19,000 square foot multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY, referred to as the 'Subject Premises'.
The warrant is related to violations of Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 371 (conspiracy) and 1591 (sex trafficking of minors).
Authorized items to be seized include evidence of occupancy/ownership (bills, mail, IDs, photos) and evidence of the layout/furnishings of the premises.
The warrant was issued by U.S. Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses on August 2, 2017.
The warrant authorizes executing agents to photograph and video record the full interior of the Subject Premises.
